  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primordial Ansatz.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathbf{L}(t)=\\mathbf{L}_0 .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Source-Integrated History.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathbf{L}(t)\n=\n\\mathbf{L}_0\n+\n\\int_0^t\n\\boldsymbol{\\tau}_{\\mathrm{em}}(t')\n\\,\\mathrm{d}t' .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Null Primordial Default.}\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathbf{L}_0\\approx 0 .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nIf angular momentum is treated as primordial, then it is represented as a fixed inherited value:\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathbf{L}(t)=\\mathbf{L}_0.\n\\end{equation}\n\nThe Trawinistic alternative accounts for observed angular momentum by integrating generated torque through time:\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathbf{L}(t)\n=\n\\mathbf{L}_0\n+\n\\int_0^t\n\\boldsymbol{\\tau}_{\\mathrm{em}}(t')\n\\,\\mathrm{d}t' .\n\\end{equation}\n\nUnder the null primordial hypothesis:\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\n\\mathbf{L}_0\\approx 0,\n\\qquad\n\\mathbf{L}(t)\n\\approx\n\\int_0^t\n\\boldsymbol{\\tau}_{\\mathrm{em}}(t')\n\\,\\mathrm{d}t' .\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nThis entry replaces unexplained inherited rotation with a source-history explanation.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
